            "body": "@heywhy Yes, it starts, but if you use it, you will see that it has the wrong root, hence, the LSP is looking only to the file you opened.\n\n<img width=\"785\" height=\"265\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/60c84736-6c77-4f43-98d8-7852be703e05\" />\n<img width=\"1004\" height=\"225\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/74c5b8d4-6ce4-4cd8-9bac-af462592fcf8\" />\n\nWhile, if you keep the correct order, it loads correctly. \n\n<img width=\"744\" height=\"397\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b8b28b54-c9f5-499f-9038-48c71d7e4785\" />\n<img width=\"664\" height=\"129\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5eb73e06-c362-4dbe-ac8c-940c987390a5\" />\n\nAlso, when you have the .git first, the LSP will index all the exs files of the monorepo, instead of only the ones in the root you are working at.\n\n@justinmk I think we should revert the PR, since the root_markers ordering is distinct from the official eXpert documentation.",
