            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The reason for the change is that, for every module opened that is outside the project root directory mix file window, a new language server instance is created, even for dependencies.\n\nUsing the recommended config:\n1. Open `apps/expert/lib/expert.ex`\n2. Run `epmd -names`\n3. Open `apps/engine/lib/engine.ex`\n4. Run `epmd -names`\n\nNow, how many language server instances do you have running?\n\n5. Open any module in the deps directory (preferably sourceerror because it's common in both engine and expert apps) of any of `expert` and `engine`.\n6. Run `epmd -names`\n\nNow, how many language server instances do you have running? And are the modules/libs in the deps folder any different from the project itself?\n\nWith the changes that got merged, a single language server instance is used throughout to serve every request.\n\n> hence, the LSP is looking only to the file you opened.\n\nIn addition, the claim here is incorrect. You could open any of the files, and the LS DB would be updated. Below is a screencast showing that it works just fine.\n\n<a href=\"https://asciinema.org/a/QqdHpKJZ13uwMoolOs3h5d3Qf\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://asciinema.org/a/QqdHpKJZ13uwMoolOs3h5d3Qf.svg\" /></a>",
