        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "\"With the changes that got merged, a single language server instance is used throughout to serve every request\"\n\nThat's literally the issue, in monorepos, we don't want the LSP to index files and deps that are no related to the root of that project. Imagine a monorepo with dozens of services, we don't want to bloat the index or the lsp-search with entries for the project we are not working at. That's why the mix.exs comes first.\n\nAlso, in you video we can literally see one of the problems it causes, it builds the engine indexes, but not eXpert itself. \n\nCorrect Behaviour\n\nhttps://vimeo.com/1115588129?share=copy\n\nIncorrect Behaviour\n\nhttps://vimeo.com/1115588585?share=copy\n\n\nCan you see that the expert builds the project after building the engine?\n\n",
