            "body": "I just reconfirmed across variants of project structures, single application, umbrella apps and monorepos like in your case (ex. expert), and only the monorepo (expert in this case) failed to emit the compilation stage which I believe is a result of the missing `mix.exs` at the root directory.\n\nThe only question I have now is what can be done to mitigate situations where a deps module is opened (let's say you're trying to confirm a particular implementation) and a new language server gets spawned as a result (with all the compilation/indexing having to happen again)?",
